definition: to leave/to depart/to separate/to distinguish/to classify/other/another/don't ...!/to pin/to stick (sth) in
he or him/(used for either sex when the sex is unknown or unimportant)/(used before sb's name for emphasis)/(used as a meaningless mock object)/other/another

sentences.english: Nothing but death can reconcile envy to virtue .
sentences.chinese: 別無他物，只有死亡能使忌妒和德行重新言好。

sentences.english: For miles and miles there's nothing but desert.
sentences.chinese: 綿延數英里除了沙漠別無他物。

sentences.english: Here is nothing but the highest esthetic of two countries.
sentences.chinese: 這裏別無他物，唯兩個大國的至高審美。

sentences.english: There is nothing but an old book in the box.
sentences.chinese: 箱子晨除了一本舊書外別無他物。

sentences.english: Life to him seemed nothing but heavy work.
sentences.chinese: 生活對他來說除了沉重的工作別無他物。

sentences.english: Life to him seemed nothing but heavy work .
sentences.chinese: 生活對他來講除去沉重的工作別無他物。

sentences.english: This is success and there is no other.
sentences.chinese: 這便是成功，除此之外，別無他物。
